title: Stefani Tolson
directions: In a skillet add onion and vegetable oil. Cook for a couple minutes until the onions are soft and tender.
Add ground beef to skillet and garlic salt. Cook over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain excess fat and set aside.
In a bowl add the cream of broccoli, milk and sour cream, corn and half of the shredded cheese. Add mixture to beef mixture and stir to blend mixtures.
In a 9x13 casserole dish add a layer of tater tots on the bottom. Pour mixture over tater tots then add remaining tater tots to the top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350Â° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted on top and tater tots are golden and crispy.
